						               													<description>Carcassone-like tile-laying game for two players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Two players try to create a recreation park together. The finished park consists of all 36 tiles in a 6x6 square. There are water and land ways on the tiles (including bridges). Some tiles show black or white ducks.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player has a different goal: The &amp;quot;land&amp;quot; player tries to build a land way connecting all 4 edges of the park without building any islands and placing two black ducks next to each other. The &amp;quot;water&amp;quot; player tries the same with water ways (and avoiding lakes and placing two white ducks next to each other).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Like in &amp;quot;Carcassonne&amp;quot;, on each turn a player draws a tile and places it next to an already played tile. At the end, there must be a 6x6 square. The players receive -1 point for not fulfilling parts of their goal (connecting edges, avoiding islands/lakes, placing black/white ducks together).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Note: The self published version features 36 cards, the Amigo version of Wege and The Legend of Landlock feature 40 tiles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
